Police are investigating the circumstances around a brazen cash-in-transit heist on the East Rand. JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating the circumstances around a brazen cash-in-transit heist on the East Rand.A gang of robbers blew a cash van up on the R24 near the Barbara Road off-ramp on Saturday.The heist resulted in massive traffic delays as police cordoned off the scene.It s not yet clear how much cash the criminals got away with. The police's Lungelo Dlamini says two vehicles used in the robbery have been recovered. We ve launched a manhunt for the suspects. Two of the vehicles that were used during the heist were recovered. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)